The paper deals with lower bounds on communication complexity in a multiparty message-passing model, which is a topic that falls under distributed computing (cs.DC) and communication complexity (cs.CC). The use of information complexity tools also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The Set Disjointness problem is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also mentions a reduction from Set Disjointness to the task allocation problem, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR).
